blockquote: Time is what we want most, but what we use worst
Healing is a matter of time, but it is sometimes also a matter of opportunity
Time is a created thing. To say “I don’t have time” is to say “I don’t want to”
It’s really clear that the most precious resource we all have is time
The only reason for time is so that everything doesn’t happen at once
Better three hours to soon than one minute too late
Time, which changes people, does not alter the image we have of them
Never leave ’till tomorrow which you can do today
Who controls the past, controls the future: who controls the present controls the past
Time is like the wind, it lifts the light and leaves the heavy
Don’t spend time beating on a wall, hoping to transform it into a door
Time expands, then contracts, and in tune with the stirrings of the heart
They always say time changes things, but you actually have to change them yourself
There’s never enough time to do all the nothing you want
In such seconds of decision entire futures are made
For the present is the point at which time touches eternity
It’s not that we have little time, but more that we waste a good deal of it
Time is the wisest of all things that are, for it brings everything to light
If time travel is possible, where are the tourist from the future?
A man who dares to waste one hour of time has not discovered the value of life
Always work and take productive actions
You either waste, spend or invest time. Make your choice wisely
Measure your life by the product and value you produce daily
Always make positive use of every second and minute
